sql:
SELECT total_distance, average_speed
FROM flight_logs
WHERE flight_status = 'completed';

SELECT drone_model
FROM drones
WHERE manufacture_date = (SELECT MIN(manufacture_date) FROM drones);

SELECT AVG(total_distance) 
FROM flight_logs 
WHERE flight_status = 'completed';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_drones
FROM drones
WHERE status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- "eagle-eyed pilot" refers to the owner with ID 1;
- "soar on average" refers to the average altitude of drones during flights;
- "highest peak they have ever climbed" refers to the maximum altitude reached by any drone during flights.

- "Guardians of the air" refers to the owners of the drones;
- "Mechanical companions" refers to the drones themselves;
- "Journeys" refers to the flights logged in the `flight_logs` table.

- "More than one drone" refers to an owner who has registered more than one drone in the system;
- "Average battery consumption of less than 10 units" indicates that the drone uses less than 10 units of battery per flight on average;
- "More than two flights" means the drone has completed more than two recorded flights;
- "Most distance flown" refers to the total distance traveled by the drone, which is a measure of its endurance and efficiency.

